l rights and feminism, that they had suffered and deserved more. From the POW/MIA and veterans’ mental health movements to Rambo and “Born in the U.S.A.,” they remade their racial identities for an age of color blindness and multiculturalism in the image of the Vietnam vet. No one wins in a culture war—except, Joseph Darda argues, white men dressed in army green.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aWhite peoplexRace identityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWhitesxRace identityxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aWhites-Race identity-United States-History-20th century. 7aHISTORY / North America.2bisacsh  aAmerican dream.  aReinvention.  aVietnam War.  aaffirmative action.  aantiwar movements.  acivil rights.  aconservatives.  afeminist.  aliberals.  aminorities.  aredistributive racial justice.  areunion.  atoxic masculinity.  aveterans.  awhite supremacy.  awhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391520 cprintz978052038144540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520381452?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520381452423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520381452/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7 